  "seoContent": {
    "heading": "",
    "columns": [
      {
        "heading": "How do I choose the right TV?",
        "text": "There's lots of incredible TV tech out there, but it can be tough to make sense of it all. So, if you want some help deciding between OLED and QLED, or HDR and HDR 10 (or if you just want to know what those initials stand for) then check out the help and advice in our handy TV buying guide."
      },
      {
        "heading": "What TV resolution do I need?",
        "text": "Higher TV resolutions give you more pixels, for greater depth and detail on-screen. Full HD TVs are bright and clear, but 4K Ultra HD TVs give you 4x the quality of Full HD to deliver much crisper picture quality. And if you really want next-level entertainment you could go for an 8K TV, with 4x the pixels of a 4K television."
      },
      {
        "heading": "What's the difference between OLED and QLED?",
        "text": "OLED and QLED are premium screen technologies that offer amazing viewing experiences. OLED TV screens are on LG TVs, and they always deliver spectacular colours and contrast. QLED TV screens are on Samsung TVs, and they use state of the art Quantum dot technology to create true-to-life images."
      }
    ]
  }
